title: Drawing, "End Table", ca. 1929–30
medium: Graphite on tracing paper, ruled border in graphite
markings: Stamp in black ink at lower right: DONALD DESKEY/ 145 WEST 57TH STREET/ NEW YORK CITY
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite at lower left: 4; lower right margin in graphite: SCALE 1 1/2"=1'0"/7635 [circled]; inscribed in red color pencil at lower right: P; dimensions in graphite.
description: Perspective, plan, and elevation drawing for small end table. Top of table in Bakelite (?) or another reflective material; drawer below in wood, with protruding surface of drawer and rectangular pull. Drawer on a frame of a different material, with rounded sides and straight legs.
